<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="398" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="13.[814,1454,194,921]" pageId="13" pageNumber="398">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[814,941,194,218]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="398">Remarks. –</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Sakai, T" box="[951,1091,194,217]" pageId="13" pageNumber="398" pagination="63 - 88" refId="ref16325" refString="Sakai, T., 1935. New or rare species of Brachyura, collected by the Misago during the zoological survey around the Izu Peninsula. Science Reports of the Tokyo Bunrika Daigaku, 2 (32): 63 - 88, Pls. 6 - 8." type="journal article" year="1935">Sakai (1935)</bibRefCitation>
described 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sakai" authorityYear="1935" box="[1212,1453,194,217]" class="Malacostraca" family="Xanthidae" genus="Carpoporus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="13" pageNumber="398" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="orientalis">
<emphasis box="[1212,1453,194,217]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="398">Carpoporus orientalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[874,937,226,249]" name="Japan" pageId="13" pageNumber="398">Japan</collectingCountry>
, making it at that time, only the second species of the genus to be described and the first to be discovered in the Indo-Pacific. The genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Stimpson, 1871" authorityName="Stimpson" authorityYear="1871" box="[1143,1449,290,313]" class="Malacostraca" family="Xanthidae" genus="Carpoporus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="13" pageNumber="398" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1143,1272,290,313]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="398">Carpoporus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Stimpson, W" box="[1279,1449,290,313]" pageId="13" pageNumber="398" pagination="109 - 160" refId="ref16623" refString="Stimpson, W., 1871. Preliminary report on the Crustacea dredged in the Gulf Stream in the Straits of Florida, by L. F. de Pourtales, assistant United States Coast Survey. Part I. Brachyura. Bulletin of the Museum of Comparative Zoology, Harvard, 2 (2): 109 - 160." type="journal article" year="1871">Stimpson, 1871</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, was originally established for one western Atlantic species, 
<taxonomicName authority="Stimpson, 1871" authorityName="Stimpson" authorityYear="1871" box="[814,1142,354,377]" class="Malacostraca" family="Xanthidae" genus="Carpoporus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="13" pageNumber="398" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="papulosus">
<emphasis box="[814,957,354,377]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="398">C. papulosus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Stimpson, W" box="[967,1142,354,377]" pageId="13" pageNumber="398" pagination="109 - 160" refId="ref16623" refString="Stimpson, W., 1871. Preliminary report on the Crustacea dredged in the Gulf Stream in the Straits of Florida, by L. F. de Pourtales, assistant United States Coast Survey. Part I. Brachyura. Bulletin of the Museum of Comparative Zoology, Harvard, 2 (2): 109 - 160." type="journal article" year="1871">Stimpson, 1871</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Zarenkov, N" box="[1156,1340,354,377]" pageId="13" pageNumber="398" pagination="63 - 68" refId="ref16833" refString="Zarenkov, N. A., 1971. On the species composition and ecology of the Decapoda in the Red Sea. In: Vodyanitzkii, V. A. (ed.) Benthos of the Continental Shelf of the Red Sea. Naukova Dumka, Kiev. pp. 155 - 203, Figs. 63 - 68 (in Russian)." type="book chapter" year="1971">Zarenkov (1971)</bibRefCitation>
described a third species, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Zarenkov" authorityYear="1971" box="[1000,1134,386,409]" class="Malacostraca" family="Xanthidae" genus="Carpoporus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="13" pageNumber="398" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="guinotae">
<emphasis box="[1000,1134,386,409]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="398">C. guinotae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, from the Red Sea and the western Indian Ocean. 
<bibRefCitation author="Serene, R" box="[1084,1248,418,441]" pageId="13" pageNumber="398" pagination="1 - 400" refId="ref16482" refString="Serene, R., 1984. Crustaces Decapodes Brachyoures de l'ocean Indien occidental et de la mer Rouge. Xanthoidea: Xanthidae et Trapeziidae. Avec un addendum par A. Crosnier: Carpilidae et Menippidae. Faune tropicale, 24: 1 - 400, Pls. 1 - 48." type="journal article" year="1984">Serène (1984)</bibRefCitation>
, citing comments made by 
<bibRefCitation author="Guinot-Dumortier, D" box="[912,1239,450,473]" pageId="13" pageNumber="398" pagination="153 - 218" refId="ref14960" refString="Guinot-Dumortier, D., 1960. Revision des genres Euxanthus Dana et Hypocolpus Rathbun (Crust. Decap. Brach.). Memoires du Museum national d'Histoire naturelle, 20 (2): 153 - 218, Pls. 1 - 12." type="journal article" year="1960">Guinot-Dumortier (1960: 161)</bibRefCitation>
that there are many carapace, third maxilliped and chela characters distinguishing the Japanese species from the Atlantic one, established the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Serene" authorityYear="1984" box="[890,1036,546,569]" class="Malacostraca" family="Xanthidae" genus="Hepatoporus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="13" pageNumber="398" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[890,1036,546,569]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="398">Hepatoporus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to accommodate both 
<taxonomicName authority="Sakai, 1935" authorityName="Sakai" authorityYear="1935" class="Malacostraca" family="Xanthidae" genus="Carpoporus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="13" pageNumber="398" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="orientalis">
<emphasis box="[1308,1454,546,569]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="398">C. orientalis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Sakai, T" box="[814,939,578,601]" pageId="13" pageNumber="398" pagination="63 - 88" refId="ref16325" refString="Sakai, T., 1935. New or rare species of Brachyura, collected by the Misago during the zoological survey around the Izu Peninsula. Science Reports of the Tokyo Bunrika Daigaku, 2 (32): 63 - 88, Pls. 6 - 8." type="journal article" year="1935">Sakai, 1935</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Zarenkov, 1971" authorityName="Zarenkov" authorityYear="1971" box="[991,1293,578,601]" class="Malacostraca" family="Xanthidae" genus="Carpoporus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="13" pageNumber="398" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="guinotae">
<emphasis box="[991,1115,578,601]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="398">C. guinotae</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Zarenkov, N" box="[1121,1293,578,601]" pageId="13" pageNumber="398" pagination="63 - 68" refId="ref16833" refString="Zarenkov, N. A., 1971. On the species composition and ecology of the Decapoda in the Red Sea. In: Vodyanitzkii, V. A. (ed.) Benthos of the Continental Shelf of the Red Sea. Naukova Dumka, Kiev. pp. 155 - 203, Figs. 63 - 68 (in Russian)." type="book chapter" year="1971">Zarenkov, 1971</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Serene, R" box="[1303,1453,578,601]" pageId="13" pageNumber="398" pagination="1 - 400" refId="ref16482" refString="Serene, R., 1984. Crustaces Decapodes Brachyoures de l'ocean Indien occidental et de la mer Rouge. Xanthoidea: Xanthidae et Trapeziidae. Avec un addendum par A. Crosnier: Carpilidae et Menippidae. Faune tropicale, 24: 1 - 400, Pls. 1 - 48." type="journal article" year="1984">Serène (1984)</bibRefCitation>
designated 
<taxonomicName authority="Sakai, 1935" authorityName="Sakai" authorityYear="1935" box="[941,1223,610,633]" class="Malacostraca" family="Xanthidae" genus="Carpoporus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="13" pageNumber="398" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="orientalis">
<emphasis box="[941,1081,610,633]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="398">C. orientalis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Sakai, T" box="[1091,1223,610,633]" pageId="13" pageNumber="398" pagination="63 - 88" refId="ref16325" refString="Sakai, T., 1935. New or rare species of Brachyura, collected by the Misago during the zoological survey around the Izu Peninsula. Science Reports of the Tokyo Bunrika Daigaku, 2 (32): 63 - 88, Pls. 6 - 8." type="journal article" year="1935">Sakai, 1935</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
as the 
<typeStatus box="[1310,1357,610,633]" pageId="13" pageNumber="398">type</typeStatus>
species. Takeda &amp; Nagai (1986) independently established a new genus, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Takeda &amp; Nagai" authorityYear="1986" box="[887,1046,674,697]" class="Malacostraca" family="Xanthidae" genus="Carpoporoides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="13" pageNumber="398" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[887,1046,674,697]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="398">Carpoporoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, to accomodate 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sakai" authorityYear="1935" box="[1214,1344,674,697]" class="Malacostraca" family="Xanthidae" genus="Carpoporus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="13" pageNumber="398" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="orientalis">
<emphasis box="[1214,1344,674,697]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="398">C. orientalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and a new Japanese species they described, 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Takeda &amp; Nagai" baseAuthorityYear="1986" box="[1169,1303,706,729]" class="Malacostraca" family="Xanthidae" genus="Carpoporoides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="13" pageNumber="398" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="distinctus">
<emphasis box="[1169,1303,706,729]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="398">C. distinctus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Both species are known only from 
<collectingCountry box="[1061,1126,738,761]" name="Japan" pageId="13" pageNumber="398">Japan</collectingCountry>
. Takeda (1986) subsequently recognized 
<taxonomicName authority="Serene, 1984" authorityName="Serene" authorityYear="1984" box="[942,1240,770,793]" class="Malacostraca" family="Xanthidae" genus="Hepatoporus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="13" pageNumber="398" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[942,1083,770,793]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="398">Hepatoporus</emphasis>
